  "market_context": "YM opens and trades lower first into the previous day's low around 47330, an open-low bullish signature. Price reaches a key liquidity level while DXY/correlated assets diverge, setting up a potential reversal back into the prior day's range toward the EQ and fair value gap above.",
  "key_observation": "Sweep of previous day low paired with an SMT divergence and a lower time frame change in state of delivery produced a reversal back into the range, but the initial protected swing was later swept before the true continuation move.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the open-low bullish signature — price opens and trades lower first into the previous day's low around 47330.",
    "Step 2: Note the SMT divergence at the previous day low between YM and the correlated index.",
    "Step 3: Confirm a lower time frame change in state of delivery (hourly if earlier, 15m/5m if into New York) with a small wick reversal.",
    "Step 4: Define targets back into the range — the EQ of the previous day and the fair value gap above.",
    "Step 5: Observe price trade well beyond the EQ, completing the reversal toward previous day high.",
    "Step 6: Highlight that the initial protected swing was swept after liquidity was taken — protected swings only hold until liquidity is reached, then they are taken before the true move."
  ],
  "outcome": "Reversal played out — price moved off previous day low, traded well beyond the EQ, reached previous day high, then swept the protected swing before continuing higher.",
  "lessons": "A protected swing is only protected until liquidity is hit; once nearby liquidity is taken, the protected swing itself often gets swept before the true directional move. Always pair a previous day low sweep with SMT and a lower time frame CISD before anticipating reversal.",
